es I'll need for the redesigned client page. This includes the client list, current user details, loading and error indicators, as well as states for validation and success messages. I'm also planning the search, filter, and drawer states for a rich user experience.\n\n\n**Defining Client Page Components**\n\nI'm now focusing on defining the key components for the client page redesign. I'm setting up state variables for edit and assign modal visibility, along with states for the client being edited or assigned. I'm also preparing to fetch client data and user profile, setting up loading and error states to manage API interactions. I'll automatically authenticate if no token exists in local storage.\n\n\n**Securing Initial Data Fetch**\n\nI've just added checks to retrieve and securely store authentication tokens from local storage. If no token is found, or if the \"me\" request fails, a re-login is enforced. I'm also now attempting to fetch client data after successfully fetching and verifying the current user's profile. Error handling is baked in to catch potential API failures during the initial load.\n\n\n**Validating Client Form Data**\n\nI'm now focusing on validating the form data for adding a new client, specifically in the `handleAddClient` function. I've implemented basic checks to ensure the client name is at least three characters and the domain name is valid. Error messages are updated in the UI through `setValidationError` if validation fails.\n\n\n**Implementing Client Creation**\n\nI'm now in the thick of the client creation logic, specifically the `handleAddClient` function. I've integrated secure token retrieval from local storage, crafting a robust POST request to the API with all the client details. I'm checking the response for success, displaying a success message, clearing the form, closing the modal, and refreshing the data.\n\n\n**Refining Client Editing**\n\nI'm now refining the `handleEditClient` function. I've added a check to ensure `editingClient` exists before proceeding, and validation to ensure client name is at least three characters. I am using `PATCH` to update the client details and providing error messages if validation fails, or if an unexpected error occurs during the API call.\n\n\n**Finalizing Client Updates**\n\nI'm now putting the finishing touches on the client editing functionality. I've integrated checks to confirm `editingClient` exists and implemented validation for the client name. I'm leveraging a PATCH request to update details and handling potential errors elegantly by setting error messages in the UI for validation failures or API issues. I've also implemented error handling to properly archive a client using DELETE.\n\n\n"}}
